Some motorists in West Acres using Koraalboom Avenue are now forced to take alternative routes due to two ditches that have been there for two years. This despite the project manager of Independent Development Trust (IDT), responsible for building the alternative entrance to the High Court, promising to find a new subcontractor to complete the job by the end of March. ALSO READ: Contractor appointment delays Koraalboom repairs According to Phasha Mokgolane, a spokesperson for IDT, they are in the final stages of completing the process of appointing a subcontractor who will complete the job, which will include covering the street’s ditches. However, five days after the end of March, Mokgalane is unavailable to confirm whether or not a contractor has been appointed. ALSO READ: Internal conflicts delay construction in Koraalboom Avenue The trenches are becoming worse by the day due to the constant rain in Mbombela. Do you have more information about the story? Please send us an email to editorial@lowvelder.co.za. For free breaking and community news, visit Lowvelder’s website: Lowvelder For more news and interesting articles, like Lowvelder on Facebook, follow us on Twitter or Instagram